{"sequence":19,"timestamp":"2026-04-17T04:43:28.518890169Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-dab560eb","body":"finding_summary: The tool-failure scenario is currently self-fulfilling and does not verify the required journaled error handling. `tests/unit/controller_runtime_test.rs:277-310` defines `escalate_br_failure_to_needs_operator`, which catches a mocked `br close` error and then unconditionally writes a `NeedsOperator` transition; the test at `tests/unit/controller_runtime_test.rs:655-701` only asserts that synthetic transition. The real close-failure path in `src/contexts/automation_runtime/success_reconciliation.rs:257-270` and `src/contexts/automation_runtime/success_reconciliation.rs:455-494` returns `BrCloseFailed` before any `NeedsOperator` update, so this test can stay green even if the runtime never records operator intervention. It also never inspects the milestone journal via `read_journal`, leaving the prompt's \"error context is recorded in journal\" requirement uncovered. affected_files: [\"tests/unit/controller_runtime_test.rs\", \"src/contexts/automation_runtime/success_reconciliation.rs\"]. remediation_hint: Exercise the production reconciliation failure path with mocks and assert both the persisted controller state and the milestone journal contents after the failure.","dedup_key":"e5cb3469f86ad8ce4e2e2d062ecab24349d51a2563ed34214c7be26b6eaf8ad7","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260417041435","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
